5./ I thought about the projects and tokens that had brought me into the crypto space and made me feel part of the community. Inevitably, @YFLinkio came to mind. And with $YFL, the unrivalled participation of one of the biggest market makers in the game: @0x_b1

4./ I gave it up after several tries when even the Neon Cat sale-tx was already minted. So I thought about turning something personal into an #NFT on-chain. This way I could finally snatch my first @prrfbeauty. Though in the end, It wasn't that personal after all.

3./ This time I tried to snatch the hashes of big #NFT sales in recent weeks and months. An NFT that resulted from the purchase of another NFT - brilliant, right?

It turns out that there are many brilliant and cunning minds in Crypto and the apes don't sleep.

2./ I researched all the hashes of every famous hack I've known of on the Ethereum chain and was presented with a lovely generated NFT each timeâ€”that already belonged to someone else. A few days later I changed my strategy.

1./ When I first stumbled across the project, only 300 $HASH had been minted. I immediately aped in and looked for hashs that I felt deserved to become a generative NFT.

And I failed. Every single tx I've entered into the gorgeous interface was already taken. I was bewildered.

0./ Now that @prrfbeauty is slowly getting the appreciation it truly deserves, I would like to tell you my own POB story about searching for the perfect tx to mint.
